        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 62,
        "summary": "David praises God as his defense, his rock, and his salvation\u2014The Lord judges men according to their works.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "Truly my soul waiteth upon God: from him cometh my salvation.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 47
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He only is my rock and my salvation; he is my defence; I shall not be greatly moved.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Salvation.",
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 35
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 10
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 42
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "How long will ye imagine mischief against a man? ye shall be slain all of you: as a bowing wall shall ye be, and as a tottering fence.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 96,
                        "end": 115
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "They only consult to cast him down from his excellency: they delight in lies: they bless with their mouth, but they curse inwardly. Selah.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Curse.",
                        "start": 116,
                        "end": 121
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 29
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "My soul, wait thou only upon God; for my expectation is from him.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 53,
                        "end": 55
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He only is my rock and my salvation: he is my defence; I shall not be moved.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Rock.",
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 18
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 10
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 42
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "In God is my salvation and my glory: the rock of my strength, and my refuge, is in God.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Glory.",
                        "start": 30,
                        "end": 35
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Refuge.",
                        "start": 69,
                        "end": 75
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 9
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 62,
                        "end": 65
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 77,
                        "end": 79
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Trust in him at all times; ye people, pour out your heart before him: God is a refuge for us. Selah.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Trust in God.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 5
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 74,
                        "end": 76
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Surely men of low degree are vanity, and men of high degree are a lie: to be laid in the balance, they are altogether lighter than vanity.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Vanity.",
                        "start": 131,
                        "end": 137
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 28
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 40
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 60,
                        "end": 63
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 103,
                        "end": 106
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 118,
                        "end": 125
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Trust not in oppression, and become not vain in robbery: if riches increase, set not your heart upon them.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0extortion.",
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 23
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Job 31:25; Luke 12:15; Alma 5:53 (53\u201356); Hel. 12:2 (1\u20135); D&C 56:16 (16\u201318).",
                        "start": 60,
                        "end": 66
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jacob 2:19 (18\u201319).",
                        "start": 90,
                        "end": 95
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 96,
                        "end": 106
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "God hath spoken once; twice have I heard this; that power belongeth unto God.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 58,
                        "end": 67
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Also unto thee, O Lord, belongeth mercy: for thou renderest to every man according to his work.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 86:15.",
                        "start": 34,
                        "end": 39
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Good Works; Justice.",
